node.text:
Thanks for all your kindness to us Aussies. Please visit us. We can’t wait to see you 🧡

Repost: @australia ❤️
We want to send our mates around the world a big thank you for all your love and support. We hope you will come visit soon!

node.text: Mumma, I holds your hand and makes sure you ok….and I cleans you. 😍♥️ Our sweet Pip.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Kangaroo Sanctuary 🦘 in Arrernte Country. May be an image of kangaroo.

node.text: Our sweet Elizabeth ♥️ Elizabeth is an Eastern Grey Kangaroo. She’s not from the desert where we are. She was rescued by a traveller about 1,500km east where sadly her mum was hit by a vehicle. Elizabeth survived in her mum’s pouch. One day when she grows up we hope Elizabeth will be released back to the wild with her own kind. But for now she enjoys the company of our Red Kangaroo baby orphans. ♥️

node.text: What do you mean you ran out of milk! 🥺 Ferris is not impressed! 😂

node.text: Our lovely 13 year old Naomi, greying around her face from beautiful old age.♥️ Naomi came to us as a tiny orphaned baby after a tour guide found her all alone near a remote fence line.
